Example 1 — Internal HR tool
Description: A company needs an internal tool to manage employee vacation
requests, with manager approvals and a team calendar view.
Estimate: roughly 120 hours split across design, backend API and a simple
web frontend. Team of 2 developers. Duration of about 4-5 weeks. Main risk:
integration with the existing identity provider for single sign-on.

Example 2 — E-commerce checkout revamp
Description: An online store wants to redesign its checkout to support several
payment methods and a guest-checkout flow.
Estimate: roughly 200 hours across payment integration, frontend work and QA.
Team of 3. Duration of about 6-8 weeks. Main risk: edge cases and failure
states from the payment provider that are easy to underestimate.
